### Job Application Coach — Pipeline API
### Open in Visual Studio 2022 (17.6+) or VS Code with REST Client extension

@baseUrl = http://localhost:7252
@sessionId = smoke-001

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Submit CV + JD — starts the Durable orchestration
#    Expected: 202 Accepted with statusQueryGetUri etc.
#
#    Inline content is used here to avoid VS's multipart file-reference
#    limitations. For real PDF/DOCX files use curl (see bottom of file).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Submit pipeline
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/pipeline
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=TestBoundary

--TestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="sessionId"

{{sessionId}}
--TestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cv"; filename="cv.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Jordan Smith - Senior Software Engineer
Skills: C# .NET 8 ASP.NET Core Azure Functions Durable Functions
Experience: Built document pipelines on Azure, led migrations to .NET 8
Education: BSc Computer Science University of Bristol 2018
--TestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="jd"; filename="jd.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Senior .NET Developer - Azure AI Platform
Requirements: 5 years C# .NET experience, Azure Functions, Semantic Kernel
Nice to have: Durable Functions, Azure AI Search, vector databases
--TestBoundary--

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Poll orchestration status
#    Paste the instanceId from the 202 response into @instanceId below.
#    runtimeStatus: Running -> Completed (or Failed)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
@instanceId = PASTE_INSTANCE_ID_HERE

### Check status
GET {{baseUrl}}/runtime/webhooks/durabletask/instances/{{instanceId}}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For real PDF/DOCX files use curl:
#
# curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:7252/api/pipeline `
#   -F "sessionId=smoke-001" `
#   -F "cv=@C:\path\to\cv.pdf" `
#   -F "jd=@C:\path\to\jd.pdf"
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
